Popover
card.desc:
The Popover control has two mechanisms for location:

####PlacementTarget

This is of type UIElement and can receive a binding (using ElementName) to a specific element in your XAML.  This is the more direct way of locating the Popover.

####PlacementTargetName

This is a more abstract way of defining the target.  Popover defines an attached property called DefineTarget which will need to be set on the target.  It is of type string and defines a name for the specific target.  By setting the PlacementTargetName property, the Popover will look for a target which has defined that name.  If it cannot find that name, it will throw an exception.
